@startuml
!theme cerulean
title UC-10 - Activity Diagram: Monitoring & Alerting

start

:1. System Operator / Data Engineer accesses Monitoring Dashboard;

:2. System displays real-time metrics 
   (Throughput, Latency, Error Rate, DLQ size...);

if (Action?) then (View Logs)
  :3. Filter logs by time, profile, error type;
  :4. System shows structured logs + trace ID;

elseif (Action?) then (Health Check)
  :3. System performs health check 
     (DB, Cache, Disk, Integration Profiles);
  :4. Display status (Healthy / Degraded / Down);

elseif (Action?) then (Configure Alert Rules)
  :3. Define thresholds (Error rate > 2%, Latency > 500ms...);
  :4. System saves alert configuration;

else (Receive Alert)
  :3. System detects anomaly;
  :4. Send notification (Slack/Telegram/Email);
  :5. Operator acknowledges alert;
endif

:6. System logs all monitoring activities;

stop

@enduml